// Topic Graph
// Interactive force-directed graph visualization of onboarding topics using React Flow.
// Nodes are colored by category; in onboarding mode, explored nodes are filled and unexplored are hollow.

FUNCTION forceLayout(apiNodes, apiEdges, colorMap, exploredSet, onboardMode) -> { nodes, edges }
  Run a synchronous force-directed simulation (300 iterations) with:
    - Pairwise repulsion between all nodes.
    - Spring attraction along edges toward an ideal length.
    - Weak center gravity.
    - Exponential velocity damping per iteration.
  Convert final positions to React Flow node format with TopicNodeData (label, color, explored, onboardMode).
  Return React Flow nodes and edges.

---

FUNCTION TopicNode(data)
  Render a small colored circle node.
  IF onboarding mode and not explored: render as a hollow circle (white fill, colored border).
  Show the topic label as a tooltip on hover.

---

FUNCTION TopicGraph()                                                   EXPORT
  CALLS: getGraph (onboarding-api), getCategories (onboarding-api), getProgress (onboarding-api), forceLayout (TopicGraph)
  Read project, mode, currentUser from OnboardingContext.
  On mount: fetch graph data and categories. In onboarding mode, also fetch user progress.
  Assign a color to each category from a fixed palette.
  Run forceLayout to compute initial node positions.

  onNodeClick: navigate to /onboarding/topic/:nodeId.

  toggleCategory: add/remove a category from the selectedCategories set.

  Compute visibleNodes and visibleEdges: when categories are selected, hide nodes/edges
    that don't belong to the selected categories.

  Render a React Flow canvas with custom TopicNode type, Background, Controls, and MiniMap.
  Above the canvas: category filter toggle buttons colored by their category.
